body_html:
Any update on this?

> find tensorflow -type f | xargs grep TensorArrayV3 |grep -v '/go/'
tensorflow/cc/ops/op_gen_overrides.pbtxt:op { name: "TensorArrayV3" rename_to: "TensorArray" }
tensorflow/core/kernels/tensor_array_ops.cc:REGISTER_KERNEL_BUILDER(Name("TensorArrayV3").Device(DEVICE_CPU),
tensorflow/core/kernels/tensor_array_ops.cc:  REGISTER_KERNEL_BUILDER(Name("TensorArrayV3")              \
tensorflow/core/ops/compat/ops_history.v0.pbtxt:  name: "TensorArrayV3"
tensorflow/core/ops/compat/ops_history.v1.pbtxt:  name: "TensorArrayV3"
tensorflow/core/ops/data_flow_ops.cc:REGISTER_OP("TensorArrayV3")
tensorflow/core/ops/data_flow_ops.cc:    .Deprecated(16, "Use TensorArrayV3");
tensorflow/core/ops/data_flow_ops.cc:    .Doc("Deprecated. Use TensorArrayV3");
tensorflow/core/ops/ops.pbtxt:    explanation: "Use TensorArrayV3"
tensorflow/core/ops/ops.pbtxt:  summary: "Deprecated. Use TensorArrayV3"
tensorflow/core/ops/ops.pbtxt:  name: "TensorArrayV3"
tensorflow/core/public/version.h://     division and mod semantics. TensorArrayV3. (12dec2016)
tensorflow/python/ops/hidden_ops.txt:TensorArrayV3
tensorflow/python/ops/tensor_array_grad.py:ops.NotDifferentiable("TensorArrayV3")

It suggests to register TensorArrayV3, but on one line, it also says rename TensorArrayV3 to TensorArray. Do these mismatches cause issues?
(I'm looking at commit 904510e in the master now.)

body:
Any update on this?
```
> find tensorflow -type f | xargs grep TensorArrayV3 |grep -v '/go/'
tensorflow/cc/ops/op_gen_overrides.pbtxt:op { name: "TensorArrayV3" rename_to: "TensorArray" }
tensorflow/core/kernels/tensor_array_ops.cc:REGISTER_KERNEL_BUILDER(Name("TensorArrayV3").Device(DEVICE_CPU),
tensorflow/core/kernels/tensor_array_ops.cc:  REGISTER_KERNEL_BUILDER(Name("TensorArrayV3")              \
tensorflow/core/ops/compat/ops_history.v0.pbtxt:  name: "TensorArrayV3"
tensorflow/core/ops/compat/ops_history.v1.pbtxt:  name: "TensorArrayV3"
tensorflow/core/ops/data_flow_ops.cc:REGISTER_OP("TensorArrayV3")
tensorflow/core/ops/data_flow_ops.cc:    .Deprecated(16, "Use TensorArrayV3");
tensorflow/core/ops/data_flow_ops.cc:    .Doc("Deprecated. Use TensorArrayV3");
tensorflow/core/ops/ops.pbtxt:    explanation: "Use TensorArrayV3"
tensorflow/core/ops/ops.pbtxt:  summary: "Deprecated. Use TensorArrayV3"
tensorflow/core/ops/ops.pbtxt:  name: "TensorArrayV3"
tensorflow/core/public/version.h://     division and mod semantics. TensorArrayV3. (12dec2016)
tensorflow/python/ops/hidden_ops.txt:TensorArrayV3
tensorflow/python/ops/tensor_array_grad.py:ops.NotDifferentiable("TensorArrayV3")
```

It suggests to register `TensorArrayV3`, but on one line, it also says rename `TensorArrayV3` to `TensorArray`. Do these mismatches cause issues?
(I'm looking at commit 904510eeaa40b0c8f982fbb679d827688cb35b01 in the master now.)
